# The sort-parity fixtures are written by the Rust generator
# (`BLESS=1 cargo test -p docgen-bases --test sort_parity`), not by hand. They are
# committed on purpose — they are the oracle that catches Rust-side comparator
# drift — but they are machine output, so review the generator, not the JSON.
#
# `-diff` keeps 12k lines of generated JSON out of diffs, which is what makes the
# change reviewable at all. The catch: re-blessing then reports "binary files
# differ" instead of showing what moved. To actually read a fixture change, use
# `git diff --text -- <path>`.
crates/docgen-assets/js-tests/fixtures/sort-*.json linguist-generated=true -diff
